But I did try to get his help
after I shot Tony.

25:39.540 --> 25:41.807
Oh, my God.

25:41.809 --> 25:43.275
Well, get it!
Okay.

25:43.277 --> 25:45.678
[ Cellphone beeps ]
Hey -- Hey, Uncle Daddy.

25:46.681 --> 25:48.414
[ Cellphone dings ]

25:48.416 --> 25:50.749
Sweet mother of pearl.

25:50.751 --> 25:53.019
Bryce shot Tony.
He's dead.

25:53.021 --> 25:54.820
You mean,
like, dead, dead?

25:54.822 --> 25:56.955
Girl, he ain't
a little dead.

25:56.957 --> 26:00.158
But Desna said they made it look
like a robbery gone bad.

26:00.160 --> 26:02.294
Cover story
is so essential.

26:02.296 --> 26:03.962
I mean, I always thought
Richie Nixon

26:03.964 --> 26:05.431
needed a better
cover story.

26:05.433 --> 26:07.633
Not everybody gets pardoned
when they get caught.

26:07.635 --> 26:09.435
Well, we over
his black ass.

26:09.437 --> 26:12.038
On second thought,
the cover-up

26:12.040 --> 26:14.640
is what always
takes down the greats.

26:14.642 --> 26:17.175
The problem is Uncle Daddy
knows the truth.

26:17.177 --> 26:19.645
Oh, shit.
He is a real wild card.

26:19.647 --> 26:21.313
We gotta get out of here
yesterday.

26:21.315 --> 26:24.650
Well, um, small issue --
we're still 50K short.

26:24.652 --> 26:26.184
Damn.

26:26.186 --> 26:28.120
Well, that's what you get
for selling those pills

26:28.122 --> 26:29.788
on a discounted rate.
Wait, wait, wait.

26:29.790 --> 26:31.057
You can't ask
the Baron's lawyer

26:31.059 --> 26:32.725
for an advance
on his inheritance?

26:32.727 --> 26:34.326
Girl, you don't
think I tried?

26:34.328 --> 26:35.794
[ Sighs ]
And he tried to act

26:35.796 --> 26:36.929
like I was a gold digger.

26:36.931 --> 26:38.196
Uh -- uh --
Yeah.

26:38.198 --> 26:39.331
Whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa.

26:39.333 --> 26:40.999
Where is the fire?
Where's Des?

26:41.001 --> 26:43.335
She's across town,
calling in an anonymous tip

26:43.337 --> 26:45.938
to the cops so the police
will find Tony's body.

26:45.940 --> 26:47.806
Uncle Daddy called me
to make amends.

26:47.808 --> 26:49.075
He wants me to come back,
and he wants me

26:49.077 --> 26:50.809
to start up
the war with y'all again.

26:50.811 --> 26:52.344
Oh, and he knows
Tony's dead.

26:52.346 --> 26:54.012
He's gonna try to pin this
on Desna.

26:54.014 --> 26:55.414
I just know it.
So, what do we do?

26:55.416 --> 26:57.950
Well, good thing I got
my crime hat on today.

26:57.952 --> 26:59.285
Here's what
we're gonna do --

26:59.287 --> 27:02.421
we get the drop on Clay
and we throw off the DEA.

27:02.423 --> 27:05.157
We gotta frame him
for Tony's murder.

27:05.159 --> 27:06.625
Yes.

27:07.027 --> 27:09.362
[ Police radio chatter ]

27:18.506 --> 27:20.306
Hey. Talk to me.

27:20.308 --> 27:22.241
In there.

27:26.647 --> 27:28.214
Oh, shit.

27:31.519 --> 27:33.118
on Uncle Daddy

27:33.120 --> 27:34.520
and we tip off the feds.

27:34.522 --> 27:37.723
The DEA get a big fish,
and it buys us time

27:37.725 --> 27:40.125
to get the rest of the cash
we need to blow on outta here.

27:40.127 --> 27:41.527
Uh, I don't know, man.

27:41.529 --> 27:43.329
Framing Uncle Daddy
just don't feel right to me.

27:43.331 --> 27:44.263
Well, I like it.

27:44.265 --> 27:45.797
Besides, you got
a better idea?

27:45.799 --> 27:46.932
No.

27:46.934 --> 27:49.535
But he's still family,
and he didn't do it.

27:49.537 --> 27:52.204
Just feels like playing dirty
to make him the fall guy.

27:52.206 --> 27:54.206
Oh, my God, Bryce.
You killed a fed.

27:54.208 --> 27:55.675
Now you worried about
playing dirty?

27:55.677 --> 27:57.076
Uh, it's not like
you're up for

27:57.078 --> 27:59.144
Palmetto Humanitarian
of the Year either, Des.

27:59.146 --> 28:00.346
Baby, listen.
Okay, listen.

28:00.348 --> 28:02.081
Uncle Daddy may not
have done this, right?

28:02.083 --> 28:04.416
But he's done so much bad shit
through the years?

28:04.418 --> 28:05.751
Think of all the abuse
he made

28:05.753 --> 28:06.886
you and Roller
suffer through.

28:06.888 --> 28:08.220
And gentle reminder,

28:08.222 --> 28:10.022
you did confess to him
about killing Tony.

28:10.024 --> 28:11.423
Ooh.
That part.

28:11.425 --> 28:13.092
He gonna turn you into
the popo for a reward.

28:13.094 --> 28:14.626
No, he --
he wouldn't do that.

28:14.628 --> 28:16.028
Oh, my God.
Yes, he would.

28:16.030 --> 28:18.964
That is a guarantee,
like a gator lurks in the swamp.

28:18.966 --> 28:20.432
Baby, look at me.

28:20.434 --> 28:22.768
Alright, Des is right
and you're in the shit too deep,

28:22.770 --> 28:26.238
and this is
the only way out.

28:26.240 --> 28:27.773
A'ight, I'm out of it.
Yes!

28:27.775 --> 28:29.441
Alright.
So, what's the plan, Des?

28:29.443 --> 28:32.177
Alright, we got
the murder weapon.

28:32.179 --> 28:35.715
Now, I just gotta get it
into the Warehouse.

28:35.717 --> 28:37.783
Alright.
When do we do it?

28:37.785 --> 28:39.385
Not "we". Me.

28:39.387 --> 28:40.852
Besides, I thought you said
you didn't want to be

28:40.854 --> 28:42.254
a part of
my "gangsta shenanigans"?

28:42.256 --> 28:44.056
Oh, my God.
Are clapping back right now?

28:44.058 --> 28:47.192
No. I'm trying to save us,
Jennifer.

28:47.194 --> 28:49.061
I gotta get in there
on the sly.

28:49.063 --> 28:51.797
I can't have you heffas
blowing my cover.

28:51.799 --> 28:54.533
And besides,
if I get caught...

28:54.535 --> 28:56.869
it'll just be me
who goes down.

28:59.006 --> 29:00.540
That's mighty
generous of you.

29:00.542 --> 29:01.807
Not really.

29:01.809 --> 29:03.875
She's the drug-dealing
girlfriend.

29:03.877 --> 29:05.877
She's the prime suspect.

29:05.879 --> 29:07.747
She's right.

29:07.749 --> 29:09.882
And I owe you both an apology.

29:11.885 --> 29:15.154
I mean...

29:15.156 --> 29:17.156
I went too far.

29:17.158 --> 29:19.291
It's because of me, Jenn,

29:19.293 --> 29:22.995
that you lost your girls
and Georgia's dead.

29:24.498 --> 29:26.966
So, let me do this for y'all.

29:26.968 --> 29:29.835
Let me make it up for you.

29:29.837 --> 29:32.037
Please.

29:32.039 --> 29:33.372
Thank you, Des.

29:33.374 --> 29:35.174
That's all
we wanted to hear.

29:36.510 --> 29:38.577
You know I want shit
to be right between us.

29:38.579 --> 29:39.711
I know.

29:39.713 --> 29:42.581
And it means a hell of a lot
that you saved Bryce.

29:42.583 --> 29:46.585
Y'all, this is the silver lining
in the dark cloud of Tony!

29:46.587 --> 29:48.320
Simmer down, sleeves.
Shit, look.

29:48.322 --> 29:50.722
Look, look, look, look.
Woman:<i> The PSS driver was shot</i>

29:50.724 --> 29:53.258
<i> and killed in</i>
<i> a robbery gone wrong.</i>

29:53.260 --> 29:54.926
<i> Police are looking for</i>
<i> public assistance</i>

29:54.928 --> 29:58.063
<i> from anyone who may have</i>
<i> witnessed suspicious activity.</i>

29:58.065 --> 29:59.865
Yes.
They bought the robbery.

29:59.867 --> 30:01.267
They bought it.

30:01.269 --> 30:02.868
Yeah, but the clock's
ticking now, alright?

30:02.870 --> 30:05.737
Based on my extensive viewing
of true crime docudramas,

30:05.739 --> 30:07.607
the spouse
or significant other

30:07.609 --> 30:10.009
is always questioned
within 24 hours.

30:10.011 --> 30:12.144
We gotta move now.

30:12.146 --> 30:16.449
Only thing is,
I need a diversion for Clay.

30:20.354 --> 30:23.555
The big question is, did anybody
figure out he was DEA?

30:23.557 --> 30:25.557
Well, he wasn't worried
about his cover being blown.

30:25.559 --> 30:28.093
He said Desna and her crew
had no idea.

30:28.095 --> 30:30.229
Still...

30:30.231 --> 30:32.231
To be safe, we should
pull the plug.

30:32.233 --> 30:34.166
Take down who
we've got already.

30:34.168 --> 30:35.835
Or not.
I mean, all signs point

30:35.837 --> 30:37.303
to this being
a random robbery.

30:37.305 --> 30:39.705
We wait a week and we can get
Desna's heroin dealer, too.

30:39.707 --> 30:42.774
I know you're trying to get
your ticket punched to DC.

30:42.776 --> 30:44.176
Pace yourself.

30:44.178 --> 30:47.713
You're the one who told me
don't hold back.

30:47.715 --> 30:49.248
Thanks.

30:51.052 --> 30:52.318
Truck was wiped down,
but it looks like

30:52.320 --> 30:53.985
they pulled
a partial print.

30:53.987 --> 30:56.322
Okay. Run it.

30:56.324 --> 30:58.124
Don't hold back.

31:03.331 --> 31:05.064
What on Earth is this?

31:05.066 --> 31:06.465
Clay made this
for the baby.

31:06.467 --> 31:09.068
Milton said Paradise was lost.
Well, now it's found.

31:09.070 --> 31:11.871
Well, I'll be damned, complete
with a beef jerky dispenser.

31:11.873 --> 31:14.540
Yeah, won't that go stale
by the time we're done?

31:14.542 --> 31:16.141
Well, that's just
for effect.

31:16.143 --> 31:17.343
I'm gonna restock it
by the time

31:17.345 --> 31:18.744
that little queen's
out of your belly.

31:18.746 --> 31:20.946
Yes, King!
Ooh!

31:20.948 --> 31:23.082
I like the sound of that!
[ Laughs ]

31:23.084 --> 31:25.617
Eh, hey, just to be clear,
you know, I'm --

31:25.619 --> 31:28.688
I'm only back if you swear you
won't hang me out to dry again,

31:28.690 --> 31:30.289
'cause otherwise,
I'm gone for good.

31:30.291 --> 31:32.091
Boy, I told you when you
called me I was outta sorts.

31:32.093 --> 31:33.425
Alright?

31:33.427 --> 31:35.294
I didn't realize you did
a good thing.

31:35.296 --> 31:39.765
And hey, we can use this, uh,
Tony thing to our advantage.

31:39.767 --> 31:41.033
Well, alright.

31:41.035 --> 31:43.369
In that case, uh, I'd like
to buy you and Quiet Ann

31:43.371 --> 31:45.771
a drink upstairs to, you know,
celebrate our reunion.

31:45.773 --> 31:47.506
Don't have to ask me twice.
[ Chuckles ]

31:47.508 --> 31:49.308
Well, um, since
I can't drink,

31:49.310 --> 31:52.578
I'm gonna go home and pack
a bag to keep here, yeah?

31:52.580 --> 31:55.180
So happy the team's
back together.

31:55.182 --> 31:57.583
[ Chuckles ]
[ Chuckles ]

31:57.585 --> 32:00.652
[ Chuckles ]

32:00.654 --> 32:03.189
Yeah, buddy.

32:07.328 --> 32:10.262
[ Cellphone chimes ]

32:10.264 --> 32:18.070
♪♪

32:18.072 --> 32:22.808
I really am sorry, boy,
about earlier, alright?

32:22.810 --> 32:25.344
I mean, I-I-I should have
been there for you.

32:25.346 --> 32:26.478
Mm.

32:26.480 --> 32:28.147
Naw, we family,
Uncle Daddy.

32:28.149 --> 32:29.615
Yeah. Yeah.
Hell, yeah.

32:29.617 --> 32:32.684
It's just when you do stuff like
that, it makes me feel

32:32.686 --> 32:35.687
like I'm the bastard Black
stepson you never speak of.

32:35.689 --> 32:37.156
Oh, come on now, boy.

32:37.158 --> 32:38.890
Don't you be
all dramatic with me.

32:38.892 --> 32:40.892
[ Chuckles ]
Alright?

32:40.894 --> 32:42.228
I just --

32:42.230 --> 32:44.430
I got a little mad
when I thought you, uh,

32:44.432 --> 32:46.766
you were on
the other side, is all.

32:46.768 --> 32:51.503
And FYI, I-I send Jerome
a-a gift ever year

32:51.505 --> 32:53.372
on both Christmas
and Kwanzaa.

32:53.374 --> 32:55.107
So, don't believe
whatever your mama told you.

32:55.109 --> 32:55.975
We -- We -- We tight.

32:55.977 --> 32:57.042
Alright, good.
That's good.

32:57.044 --> 32:58.510
Well, listen here, boy,

32:58.512 --> 33:00.179
I'll never leave you
hangin' again, okay?

33:00.181 --> 33:01.913
We family.

33:01.915 --> 33:03.249
But you got to promise me

33:03.251 --> 33:07.186
that you done with
Miss Desna, okay?

33:07.188 --> 33:09.989
You done with her.

33:09.991 --> 33:15.127
I am on team Uncle Daddy
all the way.

33:15.129 --> 33:17.396
Alright, buddy.

33:17.398 --> 33:19.064
I just got a little scared
that you liked

33:19.066 --> 33:20.800
that Quiet Ann
more than me.

33:20.802 --> 33:23.402
Boy, I mean, shit,
we need an heir.

33:23.404 --> 33:26.606
I mean, we -- we in
a high-stakes game here, right?

33:26.608 --> 33:29.609
W-W-What happens if something
happens to me

33:29.611 --> 33:32.544
and you and Jenn
and the kids?

33:32.546 --> 33:34.614
We need a neutral party
to inherit all this.

33:34.616 --> 33:35.947
Right?
No, you right.

33:35.949 --> 33:37.416
You right. You right.

33:37.418 --> 33:41.687
Now, real question is what
y'all do with that body?

33:41.689 --> 33:43.289
[ Both laugh ]

33:43.291 --> 33:45.224
What you do
with that body?

33:45.226 --> 33:47.092
Well -- [ Clears throat ]
Yeah.

33:47.094 --> 33:48.694
We, uh, made it look
like a-a robbery.

33:48.696 --> 33:49.829
Oh, yeah!

33:49.831 --> 33:51.363
Just like we did
with the Coombses.

33:51.365 --> 33:53.365
Yeah! Oh, shit, that was
a fun kill, wasn't it?

33:53.367 --> 33:54.634
Yeah. Yeah.

33:54.636 --> 33:57.569
How much shit have we done
for that Ms. Desna, huh?

33:57.571 --> 34:00.372
Coombses, Haitians.

34:00.374 --> 34:02.574
Shit, we had
that sista-girls' back.

34:02.576 --> 34:04.510
Yep.
Never doing that again.

34:04.512 --> 34:06.912
No, siree.
'Cause you back for good.

34:06.914 --> 34:09.515
Yes, sir.
Husser strong.

34:13.787 --> 34:15.120
Husser strong!

34:15.122 --> 34:17.789
Husser strong, boy!
Yeah!

34:17.791 --> 34:20.592
Back in the fold!
Back in the fold.

34:21.062 --> 34:24.996
I'm gonna take a piss.
Yeah, alright then.

34:24.998 --> 34:26.666
[ Chuckles ]

34:29.003 --> 34:30.736
Ain't this some shit.

34:30.738 --> 34:32.938
♪ Standing there tongue tied ♪

34:32.940 --> 34:36.876
♪ You better learn
your lesson well ♪

34:37.811 --> 34:41.547
♪ Hide what you have to hide ♪

34:41.549 --> 34:46.285
♪ And tell what you
have to tell ♪

34:46.287 --> 34:50.155
♪ Never again
is what you swore ♪

34:50.157 --> 34:53.425
♪ The time before ♪

34:53.427 --> 34:54.826
What the hell?

34:54.828 --> 34:56.562
Didn't your foster parents
ever teach you

34:56.564 --> 34:58.564
not to sneak
into a stranger's house?

34:58.566 --> 35:01.100
Clay, it's --
it's not what you think.

35:01.102 --> 35:03.235
No shit.

35:03.237 --> 35:06.171
Don't you try to play
a player...

35:06.173 --> 35:08.207
playa.

35:13.381 --> 35:15.314
Okay, you -- you -- you --
you gotta think this out.

35:15.316 --> 35:16.649
Hey. Look at what
we got here.

35:16.651 --> 35:18.116
Yeah, look what
I caught.

35:18.118 --> 35:20.186
Get in there.
I been waiting.

35:20.188 --> 35:22.454
In fact, I been dreaming
about doing this

35:22.456 --> 35:25.724
since the first day my baby boy
brought you to the barbecue.

35:25.726 --> 35:27.125
Yeah.
What are you gonna do?

35:27.127 --> 35:28.394
Tell you what
I'm gonna do.

35:28.396 --> 35:30.262
This gives me an opportunity
to end this war

35:30.264 --> 35:31.864
in one decisive move.

35:31.866 --> 35:33.065
Yeah, what the --
what the hell you doing?

35:33.067 --> 35:34.867
Yeah, Clay,
what the hell are doing?

35:34.869 --> 35:36.402
What do you think
I'm doing?

35:36.404 --> 35:38.404
I'm having her teach me
how to do the Electric Slide.

35:38.406 --> 35:41.073
Oh, shit, I always wanted
to learn the Electric Slide.

35:41.075 --> 35:42.208
That's a joke, dummy.
[ Chuckles ]

35:42.210 --> 35:43.542
What you laughing at?

35:43.544 --> 35:45.143
I'm about to put a hot one
in your head.

35:45.145 --> 35:46.478
That's fine,
if you want to go down

35:46.480 --> 35:48.347
for two murders
instead of one.

35:48.349 --> 35:50.583
Oh, I ain't gonna
kill my nephew.

35:51.752 --> 35:54.020
You apparently didn't get
his resignation letter.

35:54.022 --> 35:56.022
He's defecting
from your business.

35:56.024 --> 35:58.090
That's not what
I'm talking about.

35:58.092 --> 36:00.492
I called in an anonymous tip
to the cops

36:00.494 --> 36:03.762
and told them that you were
the one who killed Tony,

36:03.764 --> 36:06.699
who by the way, was DEA.

36:06.701 --> 36:08.967
You killed a rat?
You killed a drug rat?!

36:08.969 --> 36:10.168
I know, I know.

36:10.170 --> 36:12.705
God damn,
you a stupid fool.

36:12.707 --> 36:14.506
I was wondering if your mama
dropped you on your head.

36:14.508 --> 36:15.842
I'm sorry, alright?
I'm sorry.

36:15.844 --> 36:17.243
So...

36:17.245 --> 36:19.177
what you gonna do, Clay?

36:19.179 --> 36:23.115
You gonna add insult to injury
and murder me, too?

36:23.117 --> 36:25.251
You might as well raise
your goddamn hand right now

36:25.253 --> 36:26.785
and beg
for the death penalty.

36:26.787 --> 36:28.120
Shut up.

36:28.122 --> 36:31.357
Or you can just let me go,
and we can all run.

36:33.261 --> 36:35.527
I mean, how long does it take
to drop a gun?

36:35.529 --> 36:36.929
I mean, that depends.

36:36.931 --> 36:40.066
When I had to do that for
the Israeli Army that one year,

36:40.068 --> 36:42.268
it was -- it was quite
a complicated assignment.

36:42.270 --> 36:44.803
I say we give them about
30 minutes more,

36:44.805 --> 36:46.272
then we roll through.

36:46.274 --> 36:48.874
Look at you, back up in
the Kool-Aid so quick, huh?

36:48.876 --> 36:51.077
Remember what we said about
not putting our lives in danger?

36:51.079 --> 36:52.545
Oh, she's right.
Thank you.

36:52.547 --> 36:54.813
I say we wait 10 minutes,
then we get some automatics

36:54.815 --> 36:55.881
and bum-rush
the place.

36:55.883 --> 36:57.149
Pol.
What?

36:57.151 --> 36:58.751
Bitch, if you don't keep
blowing on that pizza --

36:58.753 --> 37:00.152
[ Cellphone chimes ]
Oh.

37:00.154 --> 37:01.287
Oh, no.
What?

37:01.289 --> 37:04.022
Shit's done popped off
the Warehouse.

37:04.024 --> 37:05.491
What is it?
I don't know,

37:05.493 --> 37:07.225
but just grab your
butter knives or your guns.

37:07.227 --> 37:09.428
Once again, shit has gone
sidewise for Bryce.

37:09.430 --> 37:11.697
Oh, no.

37:11.699 --> 37:12.899
Take it with you!

37:12.901 --> 37:14.567
[ Muffled ] Oh, shit.

37:14.569 --> 37:16.168
Oh!

37:16.170 --> 37:17.970
Desna:
Think about it, Clay.

37:17.972 --> 37:20.973
You're not gonna fare well
in jail, okay?

37:20.975 --> 37:23.642
The -- The -- The Haitians are
after you, the Russians.

37:23.644 --> 37:25.311
Hell, the Muslims still
ain't got over

37:25.313 --> 37:26.979
that shit you did in 2014.

37:26.981 --> 37:28.314
I don't know what you're
talking about.

37:28.316 --> 37:29.515
Ah, she ain't wrong,
Uncle Daddy.

37:29.517 --> 37:31.117
I mean, that's some
cold-blooded shit.

37:31.119 --> 37:32.251
Bean pies
all over the body --

37:32.253 --> 37:34.987
Enough.
Listen to them, Clay.

37:34.989 --> 37:37.256
Baby.

37:37.258 --> 37:38.524
Things are
getting complicated.

37:38.526 --> 37:40.859
Miss Desna's always been
smarter than she looked.

37:40.861 --> 37:43.996
I told you not to let those
Lycra jump suits fool you.

